guage=en-US|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref> and [[Bill O'Reilly (political commentator)|Bill O'Reilly]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://irishamerica.com/2014/03/bill-oreilly-broadcaster-author/|title=Bill O\u2019Reilly: Broadcaster, Author {{!}} Irish America|website=irishamerica.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref> and California governor [[Jerry Brown]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://irishamerica.com/2018/02/hall-of-fame-jerry-brown/|title=Hall of Fame: Jerry Brown {{!}} Irish America|website=irishamerica.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n\n[[Niall O'Dowd]] and [[Patricia Harty]] co-founded ''Irish America'' in 1985. Since then, it reports to have increased circulation to over 100,000 in the [[United States]], [[Ireland]] and [[Northern Ireland]]. Its writers and correspondents aim to cover news events relevant to the Irish American community, through news stories, features, and interviews. Irish America has celebrated Irish Americans from the worlds of politics, music, movies, theater, business, dance, books and academia to appear on the covers of the magazine over the years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://irishamerica.com/archives/2018-archive/april-may-2018/|title=April / May 2018 {{!}} Irish America|website=irishamerica.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nMany awards are given to Irish Americans by the magazine. The top Irish American people of the year are recognized in the selection of the [http://irishamerica.com/top-100/ Top 100]. The annual [http://irishamerica.com/wall-street-50/ Wall Street 50] highlights the accomplishments of Irish Americans in the financial community, and there has been a Guest of Honor at every Wall Street 50 event.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.irishcentral.com/news/community/major-milestone-ahead-as-irish-america-magazine-celebrates-20th-wall-street-50-awards|title=Irish America magazine celebrates 20th Wall Street 50 awards|date=2017-09-29|work=IrishCentral.com|acce